    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to the single-condition test protocol; this shortfall is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending and the clinical risk associated with this limitation is bounded by the conservative acceptance criteria applied. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The UQ campaign results, summarised in the validation report, support confidence in the model predictions. The overall credibility package is accepted for the stated COU.",
